Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with real-time control performance monitoring for multicopters, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new degree of controllability and a control performance index to reflect the control performance of multicopters, which are related to systems and control. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed switching control framework may involve AI techniques for decision-making under off-nominal conditions. 
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering aspects related to the implementation of the proposed control performance monitoring system. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper may involve computational techniques for simulation and experimental analysis of the proposed control performance monitoring system.
